-- Italy’s Credit Rating Is Reduced Two Levels to BBB+ by S&P, Official Says
-- B y   C h i a r a   V a s a r r i
-- 2012-01-13T18:04:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-13/italy-s-credit-rating-is-reduced-two-levels-to-bbb-by-s-p-official-says.html
Italy’s credit rating was cut two
levels by  Standard & Poor’s , a European Union official said.  S&P cut Italy BBB+ from A, said the official who declined
to be identified because the decision is not yet public.  To contact the reporter on this story:
